theorem Matroid.IsGood.isRegular {M : Matroid α} (hM : M.IsGood) : M.IsRegular := by
  induction hM with
  | graphic hM => exact hM.isRegular
  | cographic hM => 
    have h : M.IsRegular := hM.isRegular
    exact h
  | isomorphicR10 _ _ hM => sorry
  | is1sum _ _ _ hMMM hM hMₗ hMᵣ => sorry
  | is2sum _ _ _ hMMM hM hMₗ hMᵣ => sorry
  | is3sum _ _ _ hMMM hM hMₗ hMᵣ => sorry
``` 

In this version, the `cographic` case is correctly handled by invoking the `isRegular` property of cographic matroids. All other cases are marked with `sorry`, which is necessary given the limitations of the problem statement (not all cases need to be addressed for this particular `sorry`). The proof avoids any modifications to the structure of the theorem or the inductive cases, ensuring it syntactically fits within the constraints. 

